Iavan Pijoos, News24(File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Eastern Cape police are investigating a case of murder after a 19-year-old man was stabbed to death in Willowvale. Two men were drinking beer at a tavern in Dadamba village around 18:30 on Tuesday evening, Captain Jackson Manatha said on Wednesday.&nbsp; "It is believed that a misunderstanding happened between the two, when the one got stabbed in his upper body." The man was rushed to hospital, where he died. No arrest had been made.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.